 feeble program to achieve arbitrary societal goals. Concise and rigorously argued, Science and the Good is a definitive critique of a would-be science that has gained extraordinary influence in public discourse today and an exposé of that project's darker turn.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aEthics. 0aRight and wrong. 0aSciencexMoral and ethical aspects. 0aScience. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Ethics & Moral Philosophy.2bisacsh1 aNedelisky, Paul, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDTL Humanities 2020z978311073776908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311063899840uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/9780300240405?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300240405423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300240405/original  a978-3-11-063899-8  Yale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  a978-3-11-073776-9  DTL Humanities 2020b2020  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles